<h2>Progression of Virtual Technology</h2>
<p>
    The first ever “virtual reality headset” was called The Sword of Damocles and was created in 1962. It was so heavy it needed to be suspended
    by the ceiling and it could only see simple wire-frame model rooms and did not play games.In 2012 the Oculus Rift is demonstrated at E3 and would
    pave thwe way for other VR companies to join the market. Virtual reality gaming has only just started its chapter and has recently become widely
    available and playable. Today Oculus and HTV fight for dominance over the VR headset market. The technology increases every year and makes the exerience even better.
    With more people buying headsets and games companies are more likely to enter the market and strive to get a piece of the pie.
</p>

