<h2>Virtual Reality Technology</h2>
<p>
    Virtual Reality headsets and controllers utilize many pieces of software and hardware all coupled together to create the seamless virtual space. Whether powered
    by pc or by phone the combination of Accelerometer, magnetometer, gyroscope, and proximity Sensors all work to process the users movements.
    While the technology is amazing it comes at a hefty cost. The amazing software and hardware thatt make Virtual reality possible is also its biggest downfall.
    The PC's needed to power these headsets and games must be robust and have dedicated graphics. The PC runs the game on the monitor and diplays each eye individually in 3D.
    The PC alone at minimum for a decent expeience costs around $500. You add in the price of the headset around $300 and it's starting to look like a costly hobby.
    While it does come with a large price tag the exerience is worth it.
</p>

